</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[838,1468,1753,2012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[839,903,1753,1777]" pageId="7" pageNumber="31">Notes</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[920,1076,1753,1777]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robertsi">
<emphasis box="[920,1076,1753,1777]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="31">Bama robertsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be readily distinguished by the wing pattern (
<figureCitation box="[1030,1095,1782,1806]" captionStart="Figures 5, 6" captionStartId="8.[320,392,1299,1321]" captionTargetBox="[204,1338,143,1290]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[204,1338,136,1290]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 5, 6. Bama robertsi n.sp., holotype female. (5) Right wing. (6) Abdomen, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684873" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684873/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="31">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) in addition to characters given in the key. The remarkably long female compound tergite 1+2 and the absence of dorsal setulae on the stem vein (base of R) are characters not yet observed in other species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" box="[944,1006,1900,1923]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[944,1006,1900,1923]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="31">Bama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[838,1468,1753,2012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="31">
The specific epithet refers to the late Hywel S. Roberts whose collections (AM and FRIL) have significantly increased knowledge of the platystomatids of 
<collectingCountry box="[1207,1410,1988,2012]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="7" pageNumber="31">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
